 Butterworth - The Butterworth Regional Magistrate’s Court sentenced a 23-year-old man, Bathandwa Gcasambane, to undergo 15 years imprisonment for the rape of an 11-year-old girl. The accused was sentenced on Thursday, 12 September 2019 at Butterworth Regional Magistrate’s Court. "It is alleged that the victim was noticed by her class teacher that she was behaving strangely," said police spokesperson, Captain Jackson Manatha. "The parent of the victim was invited to the school and informed of her daughter’s strange behaviour. The child was called and she was asked her problem. "She then said that she was raped by the accused between 20-23 March 2018 during the day at Maseleni Locality, Qhorha Village, Dutywa." Capt Manatha said that a case of rape was registered at Dutywa Police Station. "The case was then handed over to Butterworth Family Violence, Child Protection and Sexual Offences Unit (FCS). The accused was traced and arrested." Eastern Cape SAPS Provincial Police Commissioner, Lieutenant-General Liziwe Ntshinga, has welcomed the conviction and sentence of the accused. She appealed to all the women and children, who are being abused to break the silence. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 